items.title: Supercontinuum lasers can lead to better bread and beer
items.summary: Researchers have analyzed whole grains with long near-infrared wavelengths using a new type of light source, the supercontinuum laser. The research has significance for our knowledge of food ingredients and may, for example, eventually lead to better quality of bread and beer.

alternate.title: Supercontinuum lasers can lead to better bread and beer

thumbnail.title: Supercontinuum lasers can lead to better bread and beer

items.title: Graphene and other carbon nanomaterials can replace scarce metals
items.summary: Scarce metals are found in a wide range of everyday objects around us. They are complicated to extract, difficult to recycle and so rare that several of them have become "conflict minerals" which can promote conflicts and oppression. New research shows that there are potential technology-based solutions that can replace many of the metals with carbon nanomaterials, such as graphene.

alternate.title: Graphene and other carbon nanomaterials can replace scarce metals

thumbnail.title: Graphene and other carbon nanomaterials can replace scarce metals

items.title: Overcoming the brain's fortress-like barrier
items.summary: Scientists have helped provide a way to better understand how to enable drugs to enter the brain and how cancer cells make it past the blood brain barrier.

items.title: Changes in teenage parenthood
items.summary: The US birth rate hasn't changed for two generations of teenage girls, but other aspects of young parenthood are shifting, especially regarding young fathers.

items.title: Students' self-concepts of ability in math, reading predict later math, reading attainment
items.summary: A new longitudinal study looked at how youths' self-concepts are linked to their actual academic achievement in math and reading from middle childhood to adolescence. The study found that students' self-concepts of their abilities in these two academic domains play an important role in motivating their achievements over time and across levels of achievement.
